cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on accelerating convolution computations in modern CNNs for image classification tasks. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories as it involves training convolution layers and learning coefficients. Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as it presents an algorithm and implementation for achieving high performance on a CPU.
